page.title: 01N and n E of North Walsham
page.content: The block is mainly agricultural land but includes part of North Walsham and Witton and Bacton Woods, a mainly coniferous plantation. The land, contrary to rumour,is not fat but undulates gently. The soil is particularly rich and suitable for growing most crops,particularly sugar beet,cereal,fruit and vegetable crops are also prominent. North Walsham itself is the market town for a considerable are and is increasing in size with several new housing developments and,although not in this block a thriving light industrial estate which provides work for many of the residents of the block,although agriculture is the predominant influence. Most of the people have lived here or herebouts all their lives but they welcome newcomers
